---
The Great Northern Forest (GNF) is a 400-square-mile dense woodland between Midgaard (south) and Kowloon (north).
Jointly governed by both cities under the Northern Covenant, signed at the Oath-Crossing glade.
The Lantern Road is the sole overland trade route through the forest, built by Ilren Voss using the Bent Mile Principle (roads yield to terrain).
Lantern posts mark fords and turns in Midgaard runes and northern knot-signs.
The Northern Covenant forbids armies in war formation on the road, restricts timbering to safety cuts, and declares shrine groves inviolable.
Two centuries ago, three Ash Winters (volcanic fallout from the Cinderteeth) poisoned streams and killed a third of large game.
The Passage Tithe system emerged from that crisis: caravans pay in grain, salt, lamp oil, and iron nails rather than coin.
Five zones along the road (south to north): Southern Verge (safe), Mosswater Bends (treacherous crossings), Ironpine Rise (dense canopy), Ancestor Deeps (luminescent moss, ancient), Northern Crown (Kowloon's Wardens of Iron patrol here).
Factions: Roadwardens and lamp-keepers maintain waystones. Mire-clans trade resin, fish oil, and medicinal bark from fen basins. Stone-antler circles guard ancient megalith rings and require ritual permission for entry. Ashfang warbands (ash-toothed exiles) raid caravans and sell intelligence.
Omens: white stag sighting precedes faction war. Red moss bloom signals corrupted groves. Lantern-and-scale motif marks Midgaard waystones. Split pine motif appears on bridge keystones.

