Midgaard treats the GNF as a managed trade corridor, not wilderness.
The Joint Oversight Bureau administers road infrastructure. Wardens under the Oath of the Counted Step confirm waystone positions.
The Northern Covenant is held in the Ledgerhouse (parchment eleven, northern drawer, third vault). The Continuity faction cites it as proof that process produces peace. The Reckoning faction notes fourteen sealed amendments no citizen may read.
The Ash Winters fill six patrol volumes documenting logistics failures: spoiled grain, collapsed bridges, convoy losses exceeding 30%. The Passage Tithe was administrative adaptation born from crisis.
Midgaard wardens maintain the Southern Verge with relay patrols and quarterly audits. Beyond Ironpine Rise, governance is shared. Beyond Ancestor Deeps, Kowloon holds primary jurisdiction. Handoff protocols fill three registry volumes.
Roadwardens answer to the Joint Bureau. Mire-clans hold equinox-renewed barter licenses. Stone-antler circles receive ritual access writs. Ashfang warbands appear only as losses in the ledgers; there is suspicion that Midgaard bureau insiders sell route schedules.
The lantern-and-scale motif is Midgaard's signature: light and measure. White stag sightings trigger doubled escorts. Red moss bloom activates quarantine advisories.
Midgaard views the forest as proof governance can extend beyond walls, but acknowledges the road shifts and the canopy erodes waystones every season.

